<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-15263] KRaftMigrationDriver can run the migration twice</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-15263</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a narrow race condition in KRaftMigrationDriver where a PollEvent can run that sees the internal state as ZK_MIGRATION and is immediately followed by another poll event (due to external call to &lt;tt&gt;wakeup()&lt;/tt&gt;) that results in two&#160;MigrateMetadataEvent being enqueued.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since MigrateMetadataEvent lacks a check on the internal state, this causes the metadata migration to occur twice.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
